an artificial brain.

104
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:51,099
Creative intelligence that can outthink
any man or any computer.

105
00:11:51,277 --> 00:11:53,006
Its insides are not electronic.

106
00:11:53,446 --> 00:11:56,074
They're organic, like our own brains.

107
00:11:56,782 --> 00:11:59,615
John, give me a number 11 matrix.

108
00:12:02,421 --> 00:12:06,255
At the risk of being simplistic, what
you're looking at is a quasi-neural matrix...

109
00:12:06,425 --> 00:12:08,757
...of synthetic RNA molecules.

110
00:12:08,961 --> 00:12:12,897
They grow. They form their own
intricate and mysterious connections.

111
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:14,589
They learn things.

112
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:17,327
Their structure
is the mind of Proteus.

113
00:12:17,503 --> 00:12:19,198
Are they alive?

114
00:12:20,139 --> 00:12:22,107
No, no. Of course not.

115
00:12:22,274 --> 00:12:25,266
Now, each one of these
holographic data banks...

116
00:12:25,444 --> 00:12:29,312
...can memorize perfectly
a dozen Libraries of Congress.

117
00:12:29,482 --> 00:12:31,416
Very soon they will
contain everything.

118
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:34,519
The sum total
of human knowledge. Okay?

119
00:12:34,687 --> 00:12:37,383
And of course,
we pose our problems...

120
00:12:37,556 --> 00:12:39,820
...and get our answers
on these access terminals.

121
00:12:39,992 --> 00:12:41,584
I have one in my own home.

122
00:12:41,761 --> 00:12:45,891
Alex's house is an electronic marvel,
completely run by computers.

123
00:12:46,065 --> 00:12:48,590
It's more secure than Fort Knox, Barry.

124
00:12:53,038 --> 00:12:54,266
Isn't that cute.

125
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:57,909
Yes. It's Arabella. She's terminally ill.

126
00:12:58,077 --> 00:13:00,443
