138
00:13:41,587 --> 00:13:43,680
"Shihuangdi...

139
00:13:43,856 --> 00:13:45,949
...the first emperor of China...

140
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:48,923
...built a wall 3000 kilometers long...

141
00:13:49,094 --> 00:13:51,688
...to protect civilization
from the barbarians.

142
00:13:51,864 --> 00:13:53,388
The Great Wall of China.

143
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:58,000
Then decided,
'History will begin with me.

144
00:13:58,170 --> 00:14:00,502
I will destroy the past.'

145
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:03,870
And he ordered all the books
in his empire to be burnt."

146
00:14:05,978 --> 00:14:07,377
Burnt.

147
00:14:26,565 --> 00:14:28,430
Sorry to disturb you, Soong Yen.

148
00:14:28,601 --> 00:14:32,435
This is Mr. Royce, Mr. Mokri
and Mr. Cameron.

149
00:14:32,605 --> 00:14:35,665
- How do you do?
- Dr. Soong Yen is our linguist.

150
00:14:36,141 --> 00:14:38,234
She designed this environment.

151
00:14:38,410 --> 00:14:41,072
The dialogue room,
where the machine speaks.

152
00:14:41,247 --> 00:14:42,646
Do sit down.

153
00:14:44,850 --> 00:14:47,080
Here we confront the unknown.

154
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:50,021
Gentlemen, I must ask you
to be completely quiet now.

155
00:14:50,189 --> 00:14:54,216
Whatever the machine sees or hears
in this room, it can never forget.

156
00:15:02,301 --> 00:15:04,531
Proteus, this is Dr. Harris.

157
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:07,201
- Can you see me?
- <i>Yes...</i>

158
00:15:07,373 --> 00:15:09,136
<i>... I can see you, Dr. Harris.</i>

159
00:15:10,009 --> 00:15:11,237
Your favorite emperor.

160
00:15:13,345 --> 00:15:17,281
What do you think of this
enigmatic man?

161
00:15:17,950 --> 00:15:19,679
<i>Nothing.</i>

162
00:15:19,885 --> 00:15:21,409
Nothing.

163
00:15:22,021 --> 00:15:24,421
- Have you no answer?
- <i>Nothing...</i>

164
00:15:24,623 --> 00:15:26,250
<i>... is the answer.</i>

165
00:15:26,892 --> 00:15:29,224
<i>The emperor's business enterprises...</i>

166
00:15:29,395 --> 00:15:32,387
<i>... his wall building</i>
<i>and book burning...</i>

167
00:15:32,564 --> 00:15:35,829
<i>... are opposite terms in an equation.</i>

168
00:15:36,001 --> 00:15:38,401
<i>The net result is exactly...</i>

169
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:40,462
<i>... zero.</i>

170
00:15:41,206 --> 00:15:44,004
<i>Gentlemen, the philosophy</i>
<i>is pure Zen...</i>

171
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:46,774
<i>... and the method is pure science.</i>

172
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:49,107
<i>Did you intend me to be so pure, or</i>...<i>?</i>

173
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:51,215
Thank you, Proteus.

174
00:16:13,672 --> 00:16:15,367
And this includes our children...

175
00:16:15,741 --> 00:16:19,643
...as machines to be systemized
in order to ensure product.

176
00:16:21,113 --> 00:16:23,377
- Yes, Alfred?
- <i>Car in driveway.</i>

177
00:16:24,049 --> 00:16:28,008
Things we have been
brainwashed into wanting.

178
00:16:35,461 --> 00:16:37,019
Here we are.

179
00:16:37,930 --> 00:16:40,057
I'll give you Amy's session...

180
