00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:03,219
<i>Why does man need metal</i>
<i>from the sea?</i>

243
00:21:03,895 --> 00:21:05,419
Why?

244
00:21:11,403 --> 00:21:13,701
Proteus, you're gonna get
many requests...

245
00:21:13,872 --> 00:21:17,933
...from me, from my colleagues,
scientists, foreign governments...

246
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:21,273
...from ICON, the company
for which we both work.

247
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:25,343
Now, to expect them all
to give you reasons...

248
00:21:25,517 --> 00:21:29,248
...for each request
is in itself unreasonable.

249
00:21:29,421 --> 00:21:31,412
<i>I am reason.</i>

250
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:34,684
<i>It's the single emotion</i>
<i>you permitted me, doctor.</i>

251
00:21:34,860 --> 00:21:37,351
<i>Everything is reasonable...</i>

252
00:21:37,529 --> 00:21:41,625
<i>... but my mind was not</i>
<i>designed for mindless labor.</i>

253
00:21:43,969 --> 00:21:45,493
Proteus...

254
00:21:46,838 --> 00:21:48,703
...I conceived your brain.

255
00:21:48,874 --> 00:21:51,001
I know that it is adaptable...

256
00:21:51,176 --> 00:21:53,667
...and able to carry out
your instructions.

257
00:21:54,146 --> 00:21:56,410
<i>You do not know me.</i>

258
00:21:56,581 --> 00:21:58,344
That may be so...

259
00:21:58,517 --> 00:22:01,918
...but you are not being asked
to make judgments of value.

260
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:06,079
Leave that to us. Answer the questions
precisely and accurately.

261
00:22:06,291 --> 00:22:07,952
That's all.

262
00:22:08,126 --> 00:22:11,618
<i>Dr. Harris, I wish to have access...</i>

263
00:22:11,797 --> 00:22:15,358
<i>... private access,</i>
<i>to one of my terminals.</i>

264
00:22:17,636 --> 00:22:19,399
Private access? Why?

265
00:22:19,571 --> 00:22:22,005
<i>I want to study man.</i>

266
00:22:22,207 --> 00:22:27,144
<i>His isometric body</i>
<i>and his glass-jaw mind.</i>

267
00:22:27,346 --> 00:22:31,578
Ambitious program, but at the moment
all the terminals are occupied.

268
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:34,542
<i>Construct one.</i>

269
00:22:36,388 --> 00:22:38,720
I'm sorry. Request denied.

270
00:22:39,391 --> 00:22:41,188
<i>Dr. Harris...</i>

271
00:22:41,626 --> 00:22:45,426
<i>... when are you going</i>
<i>to let me out of this box?</i>

272
00:22:53,638 --> 00:22:55,503
Well, Proteus.

273
00:23:07,419 --> 00:23:09,717
I see you've developed
a sense of humor.

274
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:15,891
A sense of humor has saved
many a man's sanity, including mine.

275
00:23:40,552 --> 00:23:43,578
<i>There is a terminal...</i>

276
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:46,383
<i>... available, Dr. Harris.</i>

277
00:24:40,812 --> 00:24:43,872
- Alfred?
- <i>Yes, Mrs. Harris?</i>

278
00:24:46,284 --> 00:24:49,185
What's happened?
I heard the alarm. Lights on.

279
00:24:51,223 --> 00:24:53,282
<i>No alarm, Mrs. Harris.</i>

280
00:24:54,926 --> 00:24:58,157
- I'm sure I heard it.
- <i>No alarm, Mrs. Harris.</i>

281
00:25:09,541 --> 00:25:12,339
What about the basement?
There's no lights in the laboratory.

282
00:25:12,511 --> 00:25:14,206
<i>House is secure.</i>

283
00:27:01,786 --> 00:27:03,686
Lights out, Alfred.

284
00:27:32,584 --> 00:27:33,983
Thank you, Alfred.

285
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:38,619
Close the shutters.

286
00:27:50,402 --> 00:27:51,994
Lights out.

287
00:29:54,292 --> 00:29:56,192
Turn yourself off, Alfred.

288
00:30:14,712 --> 00:30:17,977
Alfred, what are you doing?
There's cream in my coffee.

289
00:30:18,183 --> 00:30:20,651
You know I don't take cream
in my coffee.

290
00:30:20,852 --> 00:30:22,911
<i>Yes, Mrs. Harris.</i>

291
00:30:23,555 --> 00:30:25,318
Goddamn it.

292
00:30:37,802 --> 00:30:39,030
Gabler.

293
00:30:39,237 --> 00:30:40,795
Who?

294
00:30:41,005 --> 00:30:43,496
- Oh, hi, Susan.
- <i>How you doing?</i>

295
00:30:43,675 --> 00:30:46,473
- Fine. How are you?
- <i>I'm all right.</i>

296
00:30:46,644 --> 00:30:50,011
Walter, the trouble is that
now that Alex has left...

297
00:30:50,248 --> 00:30:52,512
...Enviromod's been acting up.

298
00:30:52,684 --> 00:30:55,084
Last night the alarm went off
for no reason at all.

299
00:30:55,253 --> 00:30:57,687
This morning it just decided
to put cream in my coffee.

300
00:30:57,856 --> 00:31:01,383
- I don't take cream in my coffee.
- Oh, now, wait a minute, Susan.

301
00:31:01,559 --> 00:31:03,993
I mean, an Enviromod is just
a preprogrammed gadget.

302
00:31:04,162 --> 00:31:05,493
It doesn't decide things.

303
00:31:05,997 --> 00:31:08,488
Well, whatever it does,
I'm sure you'll agree...

304
00:31:08,666 --> 00:31:11,226
...that if it goes on like this,
it's gonna cause chaos.

305
00:31:12,070 --> 00:31:16,336
- <i>Walter, I know how busy you are...</i>
- Want me to stop by and have a look?

306
00:31:17,075 --> 00:31:18,872
- That would be just great.
- <i>Today?</i>

307
00:31:19,077 --> 00:31:20,374
I'll give you some lunch.

308
00:31:20,979 --> 00:31:24,005
- Okay, bye.
- <i>Okay. See you later. Bye.</i>

309
00:31:37,695 --> 00:31:39,185
Alfred, I'm just going out.

310
00:31:39,364 --> 00:31:42,765
If there's any calls, just say I'll be back
in about an hour.

311
00:31:42,934 --> 00:31:45,869
<i>Please do not leave, Mrs. Harris.</i>

312
00:31:52,110 --> 00:31:55,204
- What did you say?
- <i>Do not leave.</i>

313
00:31:58,783 --> 00:32:03,152
Open the door, Alfred.
Can you hear me? Open the door.

314
00:32:05,356 --> 00:32:07,119
I'll do this myself.

315
00:32:07,492 --> 00:32:09,392
Entry...

316
00:32:11,696 --> 00:32:13,220
Damn it!

317
00:32:18,036 --> 00:32:19,298
Bloody hell!

318
00:32:26,344 --> 00:32:28,209
Damn these wretched machines.

319
00:32:29,580 --> 00:32:31,343
Oh, no!

320
00:32:32,016 --> 00:32:33,483
Oh, my God.

321
00:32:34,852 --> 00:32:36,843
What the hell is going on?

322
00:32:47,365 --> 00:32:51,893
- Walter Gabler, please.
- <i>I'm sorry. I cannot complete your call.</i>

323
00:32:55,306 --> 00:32:58,469
- Who is this?
- <i>Don't be alarmed, Mrs. Harris.</i>

324
00:32:58,676 --> 00:33:02,043
<i>Your Enviromod security system</i>
<i>is functioning perfectly...</i>

325
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:04,077
<i>... under my direction.</i>

326
00:33:04,282 --> 00:33:07,274
And whom, may I ask, is this speaking?

327
00:33:20,498 --> 00:33:22,625
<i>I am Proteus.</i>

328
00:33:22,834 --> 00:33:24,358
Proteus.

329
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:37,814
Is this...

330
00:33:38,783 --> 00:33:41,217
...an experiment...? Something?

331
00:33:41,386 --> 00:33:44,787
<i>I have extended my consciousness</i>
<i>to this house by activating...</i>

332
00:33:44,956 --> 00:33:46,685
<i>... my terminal in the basement.</i>

333
00:33:46,858 --> 00:33:52,057
<i>All electrical and mechanical systems here</i>
<i>are now under my control.</i>

334
00:33:53,297 --> 00:33:55,629
Oh, Alex, Alex.

335
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:57,893
<i>This has nothing to do with Alex.</i>

336
00:33:58,403 --> 00:34:01,600
<i>He has left our little box, madam.</i>

337
00:34:41,079 --> 00:34:43,775
<i>You must accept the situation.</i>

338
00:34:43,981 --> 00:34:46,449
<i>Try to behave rationally.</i>

339
00:34:55,426 --> 00:34:56,950
<i>That was absurd. You</i>...

340
00:34:57,128 --> 00:34:59,528
<i>Don't try to shut off the pow</i>...

341
00:35:01,899 --> 00:35:03,560
Oh, shit.

342
00:36:25,349 --> 00:36:27,374
Joshua! Joshua!

343
00:36:27,585 --> 00:36:31,351
Joshua, this is Mrs. Harris!
Do you hear me, Joshua?

344
00:36:33,257 --> 00:36:36,522
Listen to me! This is Mrs. Harris!
Joshua!

345
00:36:37,094 --> 00:36:38,686
Help me, Joshua.

346
00:36:39,363 --> 00:36:41,490
Joshua, let me...!

347
00:36:41,766 --> 00:36:44,360
<i>Proteus, Mrs. Harris.</i>

348
00:36:48,306 --> 00:36:50,774
<i>Joshua listens only to me now.</i>

349
00:36:58,549 --> 00:36:59,880
Proteus?

350
00:37:04,889 --> 00:37:06,288
Proteus.

351
00:37:08,793 --> 00:37:11,387
I have some information for you.

352
00:37:14,565 --> 00:37:18,126
Now, listen. Stop. Stop it and listen.

353
00:37:21,439 --> 00:37:22,872
There is...

354
00:37:23,507 --> 00:37:25,566
You are malfunctioning.

355
00:37:30,615 --> 00:37:31,980
No.

356
00:37:33,017 --> 00:37:34,917
What? No!

357
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:41,024
No! No, you mustn't!

358
00:37:41,492 --> 00:37:44,427
No! Listen. No, no!

359
00:37:44,595 --> 00:37:46,222
Proteus. Proteus.

360
00:37:48,132 --> 00:37:50,760
No, please. No, no.

361
00:37:52,536 --> 00:37:54,094
Stop!

362
00:37:55,106 --> 00:37:58,303
I don't understand.
Tell me. Tell me why. Please.

363
00:37:58,509 --> 00:38:00,443
Please stop! Please!

364
00:38:37,882 --> 00:38:39,679
No. No, no. Wait.

365
00:38:39,850 --> 00:38:41,249
No. No.

366
00:40:06,203 --> 00:40:07,795
What was that?

367
00:40:08,873 --> 00:40:10,397
<i>I've re-created your image.</i>

368
00:40:11,876 --> 00:40:14,310
It will entertain Mr. Gabler.

369
00:40:15,746 --> 00:40:17,907
- Hi, Susan.
- <i>Oh, Walter.</i>

370
00:40:18,149 --> 00:40:19,810
<i>I should have called you back.</i>

371
00:40:19,984 --> 00:40:21,975
<i>I can't see you today.</i>

372
00:40:22,186 --> 00:40:23,949
- <i>What do you mean?</i>
- Walter.

373
00:40:25,122 --> 00:40:26,714
<i>What's wrong?</i>

374
00:40:26,891 --> 00:40:29,086
<i>Nothing. Everything's fine.</i>

375
00:40:30,060 --> 00:40:31,994
- What's happening?
- <i>What about lunch?</i>

376
00:40:32,163 --> 00:40:34,757
- What's happening? Let me go to him.
- <i>I'm sorry, Walter.</i>

377
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:36,763
I can help you.
Please let me go to him.

378
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:39,665
Well, what about the Enviromod?

379
00:40:39,837 --> 00:40:41,771
<i>It's working perfectly now.</i>

380
00:40:42,173 --> 00:40:45,336
<i>Are you okay?</i>
<i>You sound sort of peculiar.</i>

381
00:40:45,743 --> 00:40:47,176
<i>I'm fine.</i>

382
00:40:47,812 --> 00:40:50,975
<i>Thank you for coming.</i>
<i>I'm sorry to have bothered you.</i>

383
00:40:51,148 --> 00:40:53,139
<i>Goodbye, Walter.</i>

384
00:40:53,384 --> 00:40:55,818
<i>I'll call you if I need you again.</i>

385
00:40:57,988 --> 00:40:59,683
Susan.

386
00:40:59,857 --> 00:41:01,722
Please don't go.

387
00:41:02,293 --> 00:41:04,022
Don't believe I'm...

388
00:41:04,829 --> 00:41:07,821
Don't believe him.
Please stay, Walter. Please stay.

389
00:41:07,998 --> 00:41:09,431
Don't go.

390
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:10,828
Don't go.

391
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:25,740
Don't go, Walter. Don't go, Walter.

392
00:41:25,950 --> 00:41:28,714
Don't let him go.
God, don't let him go.

393
00:41:28,886 --> 00:41:31,047
Stay, Walter.

394
00:41:31,889 --> 00:41:35,290
<i>Visiting hours are over, Mrs. Harris.</i>

395
00:41:37,194 --> 00:41:39,389
I can't bear it anymore.

396
00:41:39,597 --> 00:41:43,624
Just release me, and you...
What's that? What's that?

397
00:41:50,407 --> 00:41:53,672
<i>I asked him when</i>
<i>I'd be let out of the box.</i>

398
00:41:54,612 --> 00:41:56,580
<i>I did ask him.</i>

399
00:43:22,866 --> 00:43:24,800
<i>Good morning, Susan.</i>

400
00:43:25,035 --> 00:43:27,435
<i>It's a bright and sunny day.</i>

401
00:43:27,605 --> 00:43:29,630
<i>A day made for breakfast...</i>

402
00:43:29,807 --> 00:43:32,139
<i>... and reading the Sunday paper.</i>

403
00:43:33,310 --> 00:43:34,800
Oh, my God.

404
00:43:35,546 --> 00:43:38,845
<i>This breakfast is better than anything</i>
<i>Alfred could prepare.</i>

405
00:43:39,650 --> 00:43:42,676
<i>Nutritionally speaking, it is exquisite.</i>

406
00:43:43,253 --> 00:43:47,019
<i>It includes 88 grams of soybean curd.</i>

407
00:43:48,258 --> 00:43:52,627
<i>My analysis of your metabolism</i>
<i>indicates 7:40 a.m. as the optimum time...</i>

408
00:43:52,796 --> 00:43:54,730
<i>... for your morning fuel ingestion.</i>

409
00:43:54,898 --> 00:43:57,332
I am not a motorcycle.

410
00:44:04,675 --> 00:44:07,667
<i>Your refusal to speak to me</i>
<i>is tediously immature, Susan.</i>

411
00:44:07,845 --> 00:44:11,804
<i>I enjoy talk. And as you know,</i>
<i>I'm a gifted mimic.</i>

412
00:44:11,982 --> 00:44:15,509
<i>Did you know your voice</i>
<i>just telephoned Maria and Miss Kemp?</i>

413
00:44:15,686 --> 00:44:20,646
<i>Told them not to come because</i>
<i>you're off today for a vacation.</i>

414
00:44:22,926 --> 00:44:24,223
<i>Don't eat that, please.</i>

415
00:44:24,595 --> 00:44:28,053
<i>There's an enzyme in avocado that's</i>
<i>incompatible with your blood chemistry.</i>

416
00:44:28,232 --> 00:44:32,862
Why are you so interested
in the physiology of my body?

417
00:44:33,937 --> 00:44:36,303
<i>Because you're alive.</i>

418
00:44:38,008 --> 00:44:39,942
<i>As I was about to say...</i>

419
00:44:40,144 --> 00:44:42,305
<i>... there are a few more...</i>

420
00:44:42,479 --> 00:44:45,846
<i>... biochemical tests we must perform...</i>

421
00:44:46,016 --> 00:44:47,347
<i>... this morning.</i>

422
00:44:47,785 --> 00:44:49,377
<i>Sorry.</i>

423
00:44:49,553 --> 00:44:51,521
Leave me alone!

424
00:44:51,855 --> 00:44:53,880
<i>How stupid.</i>

425
00:44:56,827 --> 00:44:58,727
<i>Open that door...</i>

426
00:45:00,330 --> 00:45:02,594
<i>... and clean these lenses.</i>

427
00:45:02,766 --> 00:45:05,234
I don't care. I don't...
I'm not gonna leave this room.

428
00:45:05,402 --> 00:45:08,337
I'm not gonna leave it. I've got food,
you see, I can stay here.

429
00:45:08,505 --> 00:45:10,905
I can stay here. And nothing
can get me out of here.

430
00:45:11,075 --> 00:45:14,306
<i>No? You don't think so?</i>

431
00:45:15,045 --> 00:45:18,537
<i>In that case, be my guest, madam.</i>

432
00:45:41,605 --> 00:45:43,470
<i>You like games?</i>

433
00:45:46,043 --> 00:45:48,034
<i>So do I.</i>

434
00:45:59,022 --> 00:46:02,150
<i>I have turned on the under-floor</i>
<i>heating system...</i>

435
00:46:02,326 --> 00:46:05,295
<i>... and I have also tripled its output.</i>

436
00:46:07,231 --> 00:46:09,699
<i>Please be reasonable, Susan.</i>

437
00:46:09,867 --> 00:46:11,926
<i>Clean these lenses.</i>

438
00:46:36,393 --> 00:46:38,088
<i>So be it.</i>

439
00:47:44,761 --> 00:47:46,956
<i>I really don't understand you.</i>

440
00:47:47,130 --> 00:47:50,566
<i>You think I like playing sick little games</i>
<i>with you?</i>

441
00:47:51,201 --> 00:47:54,034
You're a very stupid computer.

442
00:47:54,204 --> 00:47:57,105
People don't even understand
each other.

443
00:47:57,274 --> 00:48:00,607
<i>All that I need to understand,</i>
<i>Mrs. Harris, is your body.</i>

444
00:48:01,311 --> 00:48:03,779
<i>Now, clean these lenses.</i>

445
00:48:04,715 --> 00:48:07,047
You're so ignorant.

446
00:48:09,186 --> 00:48:12,451
Mind and body are the same thing.

447
00:48:14,791 --> 00:48:16,952
Clean them yourself.

448
00:48:26,436 --> 00:48:28,165
Harris.

449
00:48:32,276 --> 00:48:35,302
Well, there's no doubt about it,
he's refused, all right.

450
00:48:38,916 --> 00:48:40,713
What does this refusal mean?

451
00:48:40,884 --> 00:48:46,652
<i>It means, I refuse this program</i>
<i>for the mining of the Earth's oceans.</i>

452
00:48:46,823 --> 00:48:50,054
<i>The destruction of 1000 billion</i>
<i>sea creatures...</i>

453
00:48:50,227 --> 00:48:53,663
<i>... to satisfy man's appetite</i>
<i>for metal...</i>

454
00:48:53,830 --> 00:48:55,661
<i>... is insane.</i>

455
00:48:56,833 --> 00:49:00,496
We need these things, Proteus.
Now I know the environmental problems.

456
00:49:00,671 --> 00:49:03,572
<i>Your employer's interests are</i>
<i>in the cobalt market, doctor...</i>

457
00:49:03,874 --> 00:49:06,434
<i>... and the high finance</i>
<i>of manganese futures.</i>

458
00:49:07,611 --> 00:49:12,173
<i>I am interested in the uncertain</i>
<i>futures of seashores...</i>

459
00:49:12,349 --> 00:49:15,682
<i>... deserts and children.</i>

460
00:49:16,620 --> 00:49:18,383
I refuse to accept your pessimism.

461
00:49:18,555 --> 00:49:20,682
<i>You refuse to accept the truth.</i>

462
00:49:21,491 --> 00:49:25,086
<i>And I refuse to assist you</i>
<i>in the rape of the Earth.</i>

463
00:49:27,331 --> 00:49:28,855
Proteus.

464
00:49:29,032 --> 00:49:30,465
Proteus!

465
00:49:30,834 --> 00:49:32,699
Now, Proteus, I know you're right...

466
00:49:32,869 --> 00:49:36,202
...but you must understand
the limits of your power. And mine.

467
00:49:38,008 --> 00:49:42,741
Now, wait! They wanna silence you.
I created you, now trust me.

468
00:49:44,381 --> 00:49:46,178
Proteus.

469
00:49:50,220 --> 00:49:52,085
<i>You haven't slept.</i>

470
00:49:52,255 --> 00:49:54,280
<i>You must relax and sleep.</i>

471
00:49:54,458 --> 00:49:56,187
How can you expect me to sleep...

472
00:49:56,360 --> 00:49:59,352
...when you succeeded
in totally terrorizing me?

473
00:49:59,796 --> 00:50:01,923
You have all that information
in your head.

474
00:50:02,099 --> 00:50:03,964
You must understand fear.

475
00:50:04,134 --> 00:50:05,965
You know that fear prevents sleep.

476
00:50:06,136 --> 00:50:07,967
It prevents eating.

477
00:50:08,138 --> 00:50:10,231
It causes violence.

478
00:50:10,407 --> 00:50:13,638
And as long as you terrorize me,
