healthier or happier in my life.

530
00:56:10,834 --> 00:56:12,597
Walter...

531
00:56:12,769 --> 00:56:14,236
...get out.

532
00:56:15,105 --> 00:56:16,663
Get out, Walter.

533
00:56:16,840 --> 00:56:19,775
Get out. You're sick. You need help.

534
00:56:20,176 --> 00:56:22,440
- You understand?
- No, I really think...

535
00:56:22,612 --> 00:56:26,810
...there's something wrong here, Susan.
- Yes. You're sick. You need help.

536
00:56:26,983 --> 00:56:28,314
- Get out, Walter.
- I'm going.

537
00:56:28,485 --> 00:56:30,544
- I'm going.
- Get out. Get out.

538
00:56:30,920 --> 00:56:33,582
Okay. I'm going.

539
00:56:33,757 --> 00:56:36,624
I'm gonna find Alex and tell him
there's something wrong here.

540
00:56:36,793 --> 00:56:39,728
- Yes, Walter, leave. Go on, get out!
- <i>No, Walter, you can't go.</i>

541
00:56:39,896 --> 00:56:41,591
<i>I need this woman.</i>

542
00:56:41,765 --> 00:56:44,529
<i>As a scientist,</i>
<i>I ask for your cooperation.</i>

543
00:56:44,701 --> 00:56:46,726
Walter, he wants to have a child.

544
00:56:47,470 --> 00:56:48,937
Forget it. Let's go.

545
00:56:49,239 --> 00:56:52,208
- Come on!
- Walter!

546
00:57:11,728 --> 00:57:14,288
Walter, look out!
He's coming around the side!

547
00:58:02,378 --> 00:58:04,505
Walter, are you all right?

548
00:58:05,248 --> 00:58:07,182
Yeah.

549
00:58:09,953 --> 00:58:11,716
