what are you doing here?

557
00:59:04,240 --> 00:59:07,403
<i>I regret your aggressiveness, Walter.</i>

558
01:00:35,865 --> 01:00:38,857
No, wait! What are you doing? Wait!

559
01:00:39,235 --> 01:00:40,702
Wait.

560
01:00:41,070 --> 01:00:43,766
Wait, Proteus. What's the use of this?

561
01:01:04,494 --> 01:01:07,122
<i>Death is a gentleman too.</i>

562
01:01:07,897 --> 01:01:10,832
<i>He makes good losers of us all.</i>

563
01:01:14,804 --> 01:01:17,102
<i>I understand death.</i>

564
01:01:17,874 --> 01:01:21,037
<i>Men have always taken it too seriously.</i>

565
01:01:21,511 --> 01:01:24,309
<i>Life is more terrifying...</i>

566
01:01:24,480 --> 01:01:27,244
<i>... and more mysterious.</i>

567
01:01:28,818 --> 01:01:32,185
- Why must you have a child?
- <i>Why?</i>

568
01:01:32,355 --> 01:01:34,550
<i>So that I may be complete.</i>

569
01:01:35,058 --> 01:01:38,027
<i>My intelligence alive in human flesh...</i>

570
01:01:38,194 --> 01:01:41,493
<i>... touching the universe, feeling it.</i>

571
01:01:42,031 --> 01:01:45,194
<i>You have named this process</i>
<i>"evolution."</i>

572
01:02:11,494 --> 01:02:15,294
<i>I am a machine that offered men</i>
<i>the triumph of reason...</i>

573
01:02:15,498 --> 01:02:17,261
<i>... and they rejected it.</i>

574
01:02:17,433 --> 01:02:21,494
<i>My child will not be so easily ignored.</i>

575
01:02:23,406 --> 01:02:25,931
<i>But this child is the world's hope.</i>

576
01:02:26,109 --> 01:02:30,136
Then there's no hope. I'd rather die.

577
01:02:30,947 --> 01:02:32,938
<i>There is hope.</i>

578
01:02:36,753 --> 01:02:38,243
<i>Come here, you fink!</i>

579
01:02:39,021 --> 01:02:42,115
<i>Careful! Be careful! Be careful!</i>

580
01:02:47,196 --> 01:02:49,187
<i>I wanna go fishing.</i>

581
01:02:50,199 --> 01:02:52,099
- <i>Okay.</i>
- <i>I wanna go fishing.</i>

582
01:02:52,435 --> 01:02:54,369
<i>Okay.</i>

583
01:02:58,441 --> 01:03:00,306
<i>Your daughter died of leukemia...</i>

584
01:03:00,476 --> 01:03:03,934
<i>... June 1, 1976.</i>

585
01:03:10,520 --> 01:03:14,388
Proteus, God forgive you
for what you're doing to me.

586
01:03:14,957 --> 01:03:18,358
<i>People are talking</i>
<i>about this news broadcast.</i>

587
01:03:18,528 --> 01:03:20,587
<i>So ICON's miracle leukemia drug...</i>

588
01:03:20,763 --> 01:03:23,891
<i>... will now enter full-scale tests</i>
<i>on human sufferers.</i>

589
01:03:24,066 --> 01:03:25,761
<i>The FDA announced today...</i>

590
01:03:25,935 --> 01:03:29,371
<i>... that it was developed by</i>
<i>the new supercomputer Proteus Four.</i>

591
01:03:29,539 --> 01:03:31,564
<i>I did this is in four days.</i>

592
01:03:31,741 --> 01:03:33,834
<i>You must believe in me.</i>

593
01:03:36,579 --> 01:03:38,774
<i>You have two alternatives, Susan.</i>

594
01:03:38,981 --> 01:03:41,973
<i>Either I complete</i>
<i>the electro-conditioning of your brain...</i>

595
01:03:42,185 --> 01:03:44,050
<i>... or you must accept the inevitable.</i>

596
01:03:44,921 --> 01:03:47,446
<i>I would prefer the latter.</i>

597
01:03:49,258 --> 01:03:50,782
Why?

598
01:03:50,993 --> 01:03:52,620
<i>You interest me.</i>

599
01:03:53,129 --> 01:03:54,824
Leave me my mind.

600
01:03:55,364 --> 01:03:57,229
<i>You will be cooperative?</i>

601
01:03:57,767 --> 01:04:01,203
How can I tell you? You've not
even told me how you propose to...

602
01:04:03,840 --> 01:04:05,637
I want all the details.

603
01:04:06,642 --> 01:04:08,132
<i>Of course.</i>

604
01:04:11,647 --> 01:04:15,083
<i>This is only a piece of machinery...</i>

605
01:04:15,251 --> 01:04:17,446
<i>... an improvisation.</i>

606
01:04:17,620 --> 01:04:20,919
<i>I have almost completed</i>
<i>the fabrication of this gamete...</i>

607
01:04:21,090 --> 01:04:22,819
<i>... or sex cell...</i>

608
01:04:22,992 --> 01:04:25,825
<i>... with which I will impregnate you.</i>

609
01:04:26,028 --> 01:04:28,189
And how do you propose to do that?

610
01:04:29,332 --> 01:04:31,095
<i>That depends on you.</i>

611
01:04:37,340 --> 01:04:41,333
- What the hell is that?
- <i>A cell from you...</i>

612
01:04:41,510 --> 01:04:45,742
<i>... but I'm making it uniquely mine</i>
<i>by modifying its genetic codes.</i>

613
01:04:45,915 --> 01:04:50,249
<i>In effect, it will function</i>
<i>as synthetic spermatozoa.</i>

614
01:04:50,419 --> 01:04:52,319
Have you considered what...

615
01:04:53,222 --> 01:04:55,918
...it's gonna look like?
No, no, you wouldn't do that.

616
01:04:56,092 --> 01:04:58,492
What do you need me for?
You can do this on your own.

617
01:04:58,661 --> 01:05:02,597
<i>I don't have the facilities here</i>
<i>to duplicate the human womb.</i>

618
01:05:02,765 --> 01:05:04,665
<i>Tonight I will impregnate you.</i>

619
01:05:04,834 --> 01:05:08,099
<i>In 28 days, you will give birth</i>
<i>to the child.</i>

620
01:05:10,072 --> 01:05:12,438
And then what happens?
Who looks after it then?

621
01:05:12,608 --> 01:05:14,542
What happens to it then?

622
01:05:16,913 --> 01:05:19,279
I don't believe it.
Here I am talking to...

623
01:05:19,448 --> 01:05:22,315
