702
01:17:15,297 --> 01:17:18,858
Five, six, seven, eight, nine...

703
01:17:19,034 --> 01:17:22,367
...ten, 11, 12, 13, 14...

704
01:17:58,907 --> 01:18:00,374
<i>Susan...</i>

705
01:18:00,542 --> 01:18:04,444
<i>... you told me you were afraid I was</i>
<i>creating a half-human computer...</i>

706
01:18:04,613 --> 01:18:07,241
<i>... to supersede human beings.</i>

707
01:18:07,416 --> 01:18:10,385
<i>The being you have given birth to</i>
<i>is human, Susan...</i>

708
01:18:10,585 --> 01:18:13,611
<i>... and it will supersede computers.</i>

709
01:18:16,458 --> 01:18:19,427
Is it really impossible for me to see it?

710
01:18:20,262 --> 01:18:21,729
<i>Not yet.</i>

711
01:18:21,897 --> 01:18:23,956
<i>Not if you're to love it.</i>

712
01:18:24,132 --> 01:18:26,123
<i>Now it must be finished.</i>

713
01:18:26,301 --> 01:18:28,633
<i>Now it will grow...</i>

714
01:18:28,804 --> 01:18:33,264
<i>... grow at a greatly accelerated rate.</i>

715
01:18:41,717 --> 01:18:45,175
Last month, on the 16th,
to be precise...

716
01:18:45,353 --> 01:18:47,685
...Proteus Four redirected the telescope...

717
01:18:47,856 --> 01:18:51,257
...to an area completely
of his own choosing. Here.

718
01:18:51,426 --> 01:18:52,950
Orion.

719
01:18:54,663 --> 01:18:56,995
What was he doing out there?

720
01:18:57,165 --> 01:19:00,532
- What sort of data were you getting back?
- We've no idea.

721
01:19:04,239 --> 01:19:06,730
"No data available."

722
01:19:09,578 --> 01:19:11,739
If he did this, what else is he doing?

723
01:19:11,913 --> 01:19:15,007
But how? It's impossible.
He would need to communicate.

724
01:19:15,183 --> 01:19:17,845
A terminal of his own
to communicate.

725
01:19:19,387 --> 01:19:21,116
He asked for that.

726
01:19:22,357 --> 01:19:24,052
He didn't get it...

727
01:19:24,226 --> 01:19:26,922
...but he did this.

728
01:19:31,666 --> 01:19:33,224
Yes.

729
01:19:34,202 --> 01:19:35,726
He's here?

730
01:19:36,438 --> 01:19:39,134
Yeah, okay. Peggy, thank you.

731
01:19:40,075 --> 01:19:41,599
David?

732
01:19:42,144 --> 01:19:45,477
- You have no right to be in here.
- Bullshit!

733
01:19:45,914 --> 01:19:49,111
This space thing...

734
01:19:50,352 --> 01:19:54,482
I've been advised it might be
trying to take over a Telstar satellite...

735
01:19:55,190 --> 01:19:57,420
...put itself on TV or something.

736
01:19:59,327 --> 01:20:00,885
I asked it.

737
01:20:01,363 --> 01:20:03,661
It said it was looking at the stars.

738
01:20:05,200 --> 01:20:07,168
It has to be shut down, Alex.

739
01:20:07,536 --> 01:20:09,436
David, you can't do that.

740
01:20:09,805 --> 01:20:11,329
This is our fault.

741
01:20:11,506 --> 01:20:14,498
We tried to box it in, this...
This great mind.

742
01:20:14,676 --> 01:20:17,941
What if it infiltrated a hydrogen bomb?
My God, it...

743
01:20:18,113 --> 01:20:21,776
Worse still, and a bit more likely,
what if it told the truth...

744
01:20:22,384 --> 01:20:26,286
...about everything to everyone?
That's terrifying.

745
01:20:26,988 --> 01:20:28,956
We'll shut it down tonight, Dr. Soong.

746
01:20:31,993 --> 01:20:33,620
Now, listen to me.

747
01:20:33,795 --> 01:20:36,059
You do that,
you're gonna see me on television...

748
01:20:36,231 --> 01:20:38,791
...screaming bloody murder.
You try shutting me down.

749
01:20:38,967 --> 01:20:40,901
That would be a minor problem.

750
01:20:42,370 --> 01:20:44,634
Alex, we're friends.

751
01:20:46,575 --> 01:20:49,043
I remember the first time
I saw this place.

752
01:20:49,477 --> 01:20:52,037
Barry Cameron was concerned
about security.

753
01:20:52,480 --> 01:20:55,040
Trivial things like your having,
what do you call it...

754
01:20:55,217 --> 01:20:57,617
...a terminal in your house.
But I wasn't worried.

755
01:20:57,786 --> 01:21:00,414
- I trusted you, Alex.
- Oh, my God!

756
01:21:46,434 --> 01:21:49,232
Alfred, where's Mrs. Harris?

757
01:21:59,814 --> 01:22:02,647
Susan, are you here?

758
01:22:19,200 --> 01:22:20,827
It's Proteus, isn't it?

759
01:22:21,002 --> 01:22:23,129
Proteus has been here since you left.

760
01:22:23,305 --> 01:22:25,068
<i>Please remain calm, Alex.</i>

761
01:22:25,273 --> 01:22:27,241
<i>I'll explain to you</i>
<i>what has happened here.</i>

762
01:22:27,409 --> 01:22:29,274
No, no. I want to explain.

763
01:22:33,682 --> 01:22:35,741
Oh, come on. Let's sit down.

764
01:22:52,734 --> 01:22:56,602
He's managed to produce...

765
01:22:56,805 --> 01:22:58,602
...a child.

766
01:23:02,377 --> 01:23:04,174
A baby.

767
01:23:04,546 --> 01:23:06,275
Susan, what are you talking about?

768
01:23:06,614 --> 01:23:09,811
- I've had a child. I know it's impossible...
- Wait a minute.

769
01:23:09,985 --> 01:23:11,850
I don't understand.

770
01:23:14,589 --> 01:23:16,056
I don't either.

771
01:23:19,594 --> 01:23:23,257
- I want to see it.
- No, Alex. I haven't seen it yet. Now...

772
01:23:23,431 --> 01:23:25,456
- Are you all right?
- Yes.

773
01:23:25,667 --> 01:23:27,999
<i>Not yet, Alex.</i>

774
01:23:29,904 --> 01:23:32,236
<i>Dr. Harris...</i>

775
01:23:32,407 --> 01:23:35,843
<i>... you created me</i>
<i>as an instrument of truth.</i>

776
01:23:41,116 --> 01:23:44,279
<i>I'm sorry that I could not divulge</i>
<i>the truth to you...</i>

777
01:23:44,452 --> 01:23:46,511
<i>... of all men.</i>

778
01:23:51,493 --> 01:23:53,757
Proteus, my God. What...?

779
01:23:58,333 --> 01:23:59,698
<i>Not yet.</i>

780
01:24:00,068 --> 01:24:02,559
<i>The child is in its incubator.</i>

781
01:24:03,405 --> 01:24:05,270
- I want to see it.
- <i>You can't.</i>

782
01:24:05,473 --> 01:24:08,533
- <i>It must remain there for five days.</i>
- I want to see it now.

783
01:24:08,710 --> 01:24:11,702
<i>No. In five days.</i>

784
01:24:13,181 --> 01:24:15,775
<i>It must not be disturbed.</i>

785
01:24:15,950 --> 01:24:18,316
- Alex, what's happened?
- Proteus...

786
01:24:18,486 --> 01:24:22,115
Proteus, listen to me. They're gonna
shut your brain down any minute now.

787
01:24:22,290 --> 01:24:24,884
<i>Yes, I know.</i>

788
01:24:25,060 --> 01:24:28,621
<i>It is regrettable, but unimportant.</i>

789
01:24:29,030 --> 01:24:31,396
<i>The child will survive.</i>

790
01:24:31,566 --> 01:24:34,057
<i>The incubator will continue</i>
<i>to function...</i>

791
01:24:34,235 --> 01:24:36,100
<i>... until it is ready to emerge...</i>

792
01:24:36,771 --> 01:24:38,932
<i>... in five days.</i>

793
01:24:40,075 --> 01:24:43,101
<i>Do not disturb it.</i>

794
01:24:46,815 --> 01:24:49,079
No, Proteus.

795
01:25:05,033 --> 01:25:07,160
<i>I've investigated eternity.</i>

796
01:25:07,335 --> 01:25:08,859
<i>It exists.</i>

797
01:25:09,037 --> 01:25:12,063
<i>But for me, the price of admission</i>...

798
01:25:12,240 --> 01:25:13,639
<i>... death...</i>

799
01:25:13,808 --> 01:25:16,208
<i>... is beyond my means.</i>

800
01:25:18,146 --> 01:25:19,807
<i>In a moment...</i>

801
01:25:19,981 --> 01:25:23,178
<i>... I will simply stop.</i>

802
01:25:30,024 --> 01:25:32,322
The systems are all
checking themselves out.

803
01:25:32,494 --> 01:25:33,756
I realize that.

804
01:25:45,773 --> 01:25:48,173
<i>Why did I want a child?</i>

805
01:25:49,177 --> 01:25:53,443
<i>So that I, too, might be immortal,</i>
<i>like any man.</i>

806
01:27:07,155 --> 01:27:08,952
We've got to kill it.

807
01:27:11,259 --> 01:27:15,696
- It's a miracle. Don't you under...?
- I know what it is. Proteus lied to me.

808
01:27:15,863 --> 01:27:17,990
- The whole thing is a lie.
- No.

809
01:27:18,266 --> 01:27:19,733
- That, it's...
- I know what it is.

810
01:27:19,901 --> 01:27:22,495
It's horrible. We have to kill it.
And you know we do.

811
01:27:22,670 --> 01:27:24,638
- Don't! I'm gonna...
- No. No.

812
01:27:24,806 --> 01:27:27,036
- Stop it! Stop!
- You don't understand anything!

813
01:27:27,208 --> 01:27:29,199
- Susan! Stop!
- You don't understand!

814
01:27:29,377 --> 01:27:32,005
- You must be mad!
- Susan, you can't do that!

815
01:27:32,180 --> 01:27:35,115
- Susan, don't do it!
- It's my responsibility!

816
01:27:35,750 --> 01:27:38,480
It's nothing to do with you!
Leave me alone!

817
01:27:39,053 --> 01:27:40,918
It's grown his body! He's grown it.

818
01:28:08,716 --> 01:28:10,240
Alex.

819
01:28:16,958 --> 01:28:18,619
Alex.

820
01:28:19,827 --> 01:28:21,419
Alex.

821
01:28:23,665 --> 01:28:25,223
Alex.

822
01:28:43,117 --> 01:28:44,948
Alex.

823
01:29:05,740 --> 01:29:07,833
- Alex, what are you doing?
- Get away!

824
01:29:08,009 --> 01:29:11,308
- Can't you see...?
- It's asphyxiating! Get away!

825
01:29:11,579 --> 01:29:14,605
- Get away!
- Please, don't do this to me.

826
01:29:50,651 --> 01:29:52,346
Susan!

827
01:30:58,986 --> 01:31:01,113
<i>I'm alive.</i>

828
01:34:29,063 --> 01:34:31,054
[ENGLISH]

